" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" xml:lang="en"><license-p>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.</license-p></license></permissions><abstract><p>RESUMOO artigo analisa o aquecimento do mercado de arte contemporânea nas últimas décadas no Brasil à luz das recentes transformações dos negócios, cada vez mais pautados pelo capital financeiro. No cenário de financeirização generalizada, é preciso repor o problema da natureza da arte – como mercadoria e como patrimônio cultural, oscilando entre o público e o privado.</p></abstract><trans-abstract xml:lang="en"><p>ABSTRACTThe article analyzes the heating of the contemporary art market in the last decades in Brazil through the recent transformations of the business which is increasingly oriented by financial capital. In general financialization scenario, it is necessary to reset the problem of art – as a commodity and as a cultural heritage, oscillating between the public and the private.</p></trans-abstract><kwd-group xml:lang="pt" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>arte contemporânea</kwd><kwd>mercado de arte</kwd><kwd>valor</kwd><kwd>renda monopolista</kwd></kwd-group><kwd-group xml:lang="en" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>contemporary art</kwd><kwd>art market</kwd><kwd>value</kwd><kwd>monopoly rent</kwd></kwd-group><counts><fig-count count="0"/><table-count count="0"/><equation-count count="0"/><ref-count count="0"/><page-count count="16"/></counts></article-meta></front></article>